Package ohos.vibrator.bean

Class VibrationPattern

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.vibrator.bean.VibrationPattern

  • public class VibrationPattern
extends Object
    Defines the vibration effects of vibrators.

    You can use this class to create a one-shot or periodic vibration and set vibration parameters, such as the vibration counts, duration, and intensity.

    Since:
    1
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.Sensors#MISC_DEVICE

    • Method Detail

      • createSingle

        public static final VibrationPattern createSingle​(int duration,
                                                  int intensity)
        Creates a one-shot vibration effect.

        This method is used to control a vibrator to vibrate at a specified intensity throughout a specified duration. Its return result is used to pass a value to the VibrationPattern parameter in the VibratorAgent.start(int, VibrationPattern) method to customize the effect of a one-shot vibration.

        Parameters:
        duration - Indicates the duration of a one-shot vibration, in milliseconds. The value range is 0-1800000 ms (30 minutes).
        intensity - Indicates the vibration intensity. The value range is 0–255.
        Returns:
        Returns the effect of a one-shot vibration. The return value will be used in the VibratorAgent parameter for a custom vibration.
        Since:
        1
        See Also:
        VibratorAgent

      • createPeriod

        public static final VibrationPattern createPeriod​(int[] timing,
                                                  int[] intensities,
                                                  int count)
        Creates a periodic vibration effect with a given timing sequence and intensity.

        This method is used to control a vibrator to vibrate for specified counts at a given intensity based on the timing sequence. When the specified number of counts is reached, the vibrator stops vibrating. Its return result is used to pass a value to the VibrationPattern parameter in the VibratorAgent.start(int, VibrationPattern) method to customize the effect of a periodic vibration.

        Parameters:
        timing - Indicates the timing sequence for the vibration, in milliseconds. The timing sequence is presented by alternating values in an array. The first value in the array is the period to wait before vibrating, the second value in the array is the duration that the vibration lasts, and so on. The value range is 0-1800000 ms (30 minutes), and the total vibration duration cannot exceed 1800000 ms (30 minutes). For example, timing sequence array {1000,2000,2000,1000} represents that the vibrator stops vibration for 1000 ms, vibrates for 2000 ms, then stops for 2000 ms, and vibrates again for 1000 ms.
        intensities - Indicates the vibration intensity. The value range is 0–255. The values for the vibration intensity are set in accordance with the values for the timing sequence. For example, the timing sequence array is {1000,2000,2000,1000} and the vibration intensity array is {120,200,110,125}. When the vibrator stops vibration, values 120 and 110 in the intensity array are invalid; when the vibrator is vibrating, values 200 and 125 are valid and the vibration lasts 2000 ms and 1000 ms, respectively.
        count - Indicates the number of times for the vibrator to repeat vibration. The value range is 0–100.
        Returns:
        Returns the effect of a periodic vibration. The return value will be used in the VibratorAgent parameter for a custom vibration.
        Since:
        1
        See Also:
        VibratorAgent
